Minister of Science and Technology, Dr. Ogbonnaya Onu has stated that technological incubation centres established across the country would supply labour for new investments being envisaged in the near future. He disclosed this at the commissioning of the Technological Incubation Centre in Lafia, Nasarawa state.Onu, who said that the newly established incubation centres would help startups from Micro levels to small, medium and large business enterprises, stressed the need for the startups because according to him, most business enterprises started at the micro-level. “This centre will help produce the next generation of Dangote’s and International businessmen in Nigeria. The National Board for Technological Incubation (NBTI), gathers together all research findings from the ministry and other relevant institutions, with the aim of commercialising them,” he said.Onu added that the major essence of the establishment of the incubation centres was to ensure and improve productivity in the country. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .